reviews.text: Luckily the food is half decent. I ordered online for pick up and it said it should take 30 mins. Thats a normal time for pick up. I get there at 30 mins and sat at the bar near the register for 15 mins until someone would speak to me. The staff was RUDE. I am still here now 15 mins more for a total of 30 mins now still no food. This place is bad.

There is no shortage of tasty breakfast restaurants in this area, but this place really is great. I (and a few of the people I was with) made a few annoying modifications to my breakfast sandwich and my server handled it wonderfully. The food came out fast and our server was very attentive.
My bacon, egg, and cheese sandwich on a bagel was very good and homefries were exceptional. Some places like this have homefries that were previously frozen and lame, these were fresh and nicely seasoned. A person I was with got a toasted sandwich on sourdough and it was perfectly cooked, big and golden brown. 
It's a pleasant little space with lots of nice outdoor seating, and the food is all very reasonably priced. Ignore the old negative reviews, whatever the problem was, something has changed and this place is awesome.

I went to this place to try it out. The decor reminded me of a mix between texas and old timey gas stations :/ but I guess if that's what they are going for, okay. The place had nobody else in it, but it took a while for the waitress to come and ask for our order. I got the strawberry cheesecake french toast. I was expecting a regular french toast with cheesecake filling and fresh strawberries. What I got was really greasy, with a little bit of cheesecake filling.. and drowning in canned strawberry "pie filling". I call it pie filling because I am not entirely sure what it is supposed to be. It was an artificial tasting bright red smooth jelly-like textured substance.. almost jello. I took a few bites but felt so unhealthy I could not finish it. The waitress asked if the food was delicious and I said yes because I didn't want to sound rude.

reviews.text: Absolutely the worst food we've ever had & way overpriced. General Tso's chicken, sesame chicken, fried rice, lo mein, and pork egg rolls. The chicken was not breaded & the seasonings were horrible. The "fried rice" was brown rice with nothing else in it. The lo mein had absolutely no flavor. The chicken dishes had more broccoli than chicken. The egg roll tasted like marijuana (not a taste that I'm fond of).  My husband bit into what looked like a piece of bone. We will never go back again. I wish I could give negative stars

I got the sushi and sashimi lunch special. Most of it was quite bland. The rice tasted funny and the fish on the sushi looked and tasted old. The rice is such an important part of sushi! I've had sushi all over the world and this place is your typical Asian American place with a 20% authentic feel. I'm not a fusion fan. 

Now, the people I saw there are all not Japanese which is a sign not to get Japanese cuisine but I was craving fish. The salmon and tuna sashimi were very fresh and yummy however! The miso soup was good too but was a tad watery. 

This is a mixed review because I feel mixed about it.

Asian Cafe food is delicious! Don't understand the negative reviews. They delivered very timely as well. We ordered many items from the menu and all the food was very good. They are comparable to my favorite Chinese restaurant in Malvern so I'm very happy we have a place close by. We will definitely order here again!

reviews.text:
Businesses are forgetting one major point: Customers make the business. No customers, no business!! This place leaves a lot to desire, a lot! No greeting customers. Food blah! Extra greasy, with a bad after taste! The rice tastes like it was days old and is being used over and over again! Just no bueño!
And the picture showing their takeout containers and presentation, definitely wasn't our experience. The containers were styrofoam and the food, sloppily prepared!

Really cheap? Pretty fast delivery? Open late? Yes to all three.

Is the food good? Not really. We were either outright unhappy (one dish went into the trash untouched) or just unimpressed with China Star. The fried rice was nothing special, and the egg drop soup was totally bland. Probably there are better Chinese takeout spots around here.
The previous reviews had me worried so one day I took the chance and was actually surprise with how good the food was. I'll def come back

I would give negative stars if I could the workers personality are bad I asked if can add extra boba rudely said no extra allowed I also came three days in a row and first time they told me the waffle machine was broken second day they told me it was being cleaned and third day said oh it was not plugged in. And need to be plugged in and they they were busy so ...
They have honey lemon green tea, but I could not get just honey green tea. That was odd to me. I didn't get anything and was disappointed. I really wanted to like this place.

name: Panera Bread
description: American (New), Restaurants, Bakeries, Food, Sandwiches, Soup, Salad, Bagels, Breakfast & Brunch

reviews.text:
Really nice atmosphere. Very clean and friendly staff. 

In particular, there was a woman walking around checking in with customers as they ate. Her name was Christina. She was fantastic!! Really going the extra mile to provide top-level customer service to the customers.

In the spring of 2011 I worked near this location.  Every Wednesday a co-worker would pick up the lunches for us.  The food was fairly decent which is why this is a 2 star as opposed to a 1 star review.  My issue is that the business REFUSES to post pricing on their menus.  I just looked @ Panera's website and there is STILL no prices whatever on their menus.  People are on fixed budgets and have fixed means of income for crying out loud?!  I would therefore be @ the mercy of the honesty of the then co-worker as to how much I would be charged - thankfully said person is honest.  If I remember correctly when she called in the orders she was not apprised of the prices until she went over to pick up the stuff - she's much more comfortable about driving on Street Road than I am or I'd go over to check it out myself.  I am surprised no one mentioned this as you would think there would be local or state legislation requiring pricing be placed on menus - printed or online.  This BTW is the ONLY food business I ever encountered this with.  Even today (1/23/17) there is NO pricing on their online menu; they tout having a transparent menu - without pricing as far as I'm concerned it is NOT transparent enough!  I neither live nor work near one of their locations currently and with NO pricing posted I definitely will not go out of my way to patronize these locations.

Ordered lunch from here. Delivery was really fast, so good work by the driver. 
Everything else was pretty lacking. Got my cookie order wrong (ordered choc. chip, got oatmeal raisin). 
The tortellini was dry and hard in places, indicative of sitting in a steamer tray for too long. Portions were really quite stingy for twenty bucks' worth of food. Everything was pretty bland considering how much salt is in it. 
It's a chain restaurant, so my expectations were set accordingly. Even then, I give it a "D".

reviews.text: I have been here a few times and while I haven't experienced an unhelpful staff, I have experienced a lack of condimints and ingredients. Avoid if possible

I'm severely handicapped & took a recent trip to this Subway to order a sub. There was a sign on the front door that said to use the side door. There is no side door. There is only a front door & a back door. To get to the back door, you must either walk through the grass to the right, or walk in the middle of the road, because there is no sidewalk on the side of Subway, along with the non existent side door. I could see a few customers inside, & the lady employee, & I tried waving at them to get someone to open the front door, as I cannot open doors without assistance, & everyone inside either laughed & shook  their heads, or pretended not to hear me. Some junkie finally opened the door & the laughing customers kept laughing & making comments. I asked if my being handicapped amuses them & they said it's hilarious because I was causing a scene. I wasn't originally causing a scene. I explained that there's no side door & I'm not struggling to get stuck in the grass or in middle of the road & get hit by a car. Employee was also laughing her @$$ off & I said to let me out. Door was locked & she laughed & said she was too busy to let me out. 
Her excuse for the front door being locked was because she's working alone & doesn't want to get robbed. Nobody can park out front, only in back, so, if she was going to get robbed, getaway car would be out back. There's nowhere for a robber to run away out front, except right into the 5 way intersection directly out front. Horrible things were said to me by the customers (ask me)
I'm never going back there. She can go rot like Jared!
Been here a few times since moving in to Elsmere. I've found the staff super friendly and nice. Every time I've gone in the offerings are fresh and they've always had what I wanted.

name: Duck Donuts
description: Coffee & Tea, Donuts, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Food

reviews.text:
Stopped by for Sunday morning breakfast- along with many others, as the line reached the door when we arrived. On the right when you walk in are paper menus and pencils, with which you record your order. There are a few favorites listed at the top, and then you have the option to create your own combos by choosing a coating, topping, and a drizzle. The donuts are made fresh to order and the line moves along relatively quickly, especially when you're distracted by all the choices on the menu.

Once we placed our order, the donuts were made pretty quickly. However, it did take quite a bit for them to make the coffee. Once the donuts are done, they showed us the box and asked if they looked good, upon which my sister and I requested that they add more powder onto our powder donuts (which they did).

I ordered one powder and one with chocolate coating/chocolate topping/fudge drizzle. The donuts were absolutely delicious! My sister enjoyed her powdered, and her graham cracker sprinkled creation was tasty as well. My boyfriend enjoyed his pb & jelly donut, and he was surprised that he also liked the bacon donut.

There's a fridge with some beverages such as apple juice and etc, but I prefer my donuts with a cold milk. Milks were only sold via tiny carton, so I had to buy 2. My only suggestion is that they supply the fridge with larger cartons. I'm sure we'll be back again soon.

Such a fan of this place!  Let's start with prices -$1.98 for a single donut and right now they have a BOGO offer- 2 donuts for the price of 1!  The donuts are freshly made in front of you and they always ask for your approval before you leave with your donuts.  They also sell milk and a variety of drinks.  My favorite is the glazed maple bacon.. glazed donut with real crunch bacon topping drizzled with a maple flavoring- SO YUM! Second fav is the apple strudel.. def worth the price
Delish!! Fresh made, great ingredients. So good! Perfect treat. We got a few of the suggested mix - boardwalk donut and the maple bacon and then my daughter made her own. Everyone was satisfied!

name: Pizza Land
address: 202 Holland Rd, Ste 208, Wawa Shopping Ctr
description: Restaurants, Food Delivery Services, Food, Italian, Pizza

reviews.text: Everyone is so nice in this pizza shop! I have a slice of their pizza maybe 1-2 times a week! Living in the northeast and working in holland I can't find pizza that's actually good! This place is by far the best around all the way down to the northeast! The chicken parm sandwich is my top fav, mozzarella sticks are good with good dipping sauce, plain pizza delish, Sicilian is amazing, and try the spinach tomato pie, you won't be disappointed! Delivery guys are all great too!

So now that I've tried more of their menu, I'm tempted to knock them down a star. However, the service there is very helpful and friendly, so they get to keep a star for that.

Their regular slices  are very mediocre, teetering towards the side of bad. Crispy and burnt, the sauce is nothing special and the toppings just fall right off. I can eat them, but I'd rather not. Stick to Sicilian if you're getting a pie here. The garlic knots are large, I'll give them that, but very dry unless you put the (extremely spicy) oil at the counter on them to moisten them up. Plus, there's not enough garlic in them.

A very mediocre experience at this place, which is a shame.

TWO SLICE SPECIAL REVIEW ONLY

The price at $4.99 for two large slices of pizza and a soft drink was excellent.  The size of the slices was also more than expected. The service was friendly.  The room was small, with only two tables for those who want to eat their pizza just out of the oven when it is at its prime. So, this is basically a take out joint. 

We wanted a quick bite to tide us over until dinner. A slice apiece and sharing the drink was our intention. 

I requested that the reheat be "well done," in order to bring the ingredients back to life after sitting on display. 

What we received were slices that were not hot in the center where the cheese was thickest. That was likely due to the excessive amount of cheese piled onto the pie, out of proportion to the tomato sauce which seemed sparingly used. The result was pizza that could not be picked up by the crust because it was too heavy on the topside.  The taste was weak because of the cheese/sauce imbalance, and perhaps the quality of the cheese and sauce themselves.  The crust would have been improved with a little salt added to the dough.  

Not an impressive effort by Pizza Land.

name: Kung Fu Tea
description: Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Bubble Tea, Coffee & Tea

reviews.text: The restaurant is very clean and decently big! There is adequate seating for all party sizes. The staff is attentive and helpful with your order. The bubble tea options are very large and very customizable. The tea itself is delicious and good quality. The most noteworthy thing about Kung Fu Tea is the bubbles. You can go to a million bubble tea locations as many times as you choose and consistently receive boba that is not quite right, or constantly different in quality. But this is not an issue at Kung Fu Tea. The bubbles are always perfectly made and consistently made. No matter when you go or how often you frequent the place, you can count on receiving perfectly cooked, delicious boba in your bubble tea. If chains turn you off to trying this bubble tea, I can assure you that quality is not affected by that factor. It is really worth a try!
Asked what one of the workers what he would recommend I ended up getting the mango matcha tea with boba it was fantastic, quick tasty and a nice staff!

First time here and gotta say I was disappointed. Service was slightly slow and they had a sign showing they accepted credit cards but they actually don't yet. I'll give it a 3 out of 5 since I wasn't impressed. Drink was ok...so may give it another try and update when I do. You choose a base drink, then add in bubbles or jelly at .50¢ additional and wait for it. You can customize sweetness level and ice level as well.

Cash only until they get their credit card system up...they should've put a sign up though.

reviews.text:
The food was "okay", but I wouldn't give 2 stars just off that. I felt the customer service was poor. First off, let me say that I know working in a mall can suck. I did it back in college in Atlanta, GA. I worked at a mall called Perimeter Mall, but I digress... With the typical mallrat children/teenagers, low life's, and generally weird people frequenting any mall in America - there comes some stress to the mall employees. However, this is the job you chose. Out of tons of other jobs...I might add. So, I feel it's important to do your job well and amicably. Oh yeah, I feel like the "amicable" part is part of the job - not a result that you get when your lucky, or attractive, or intelligent, etc. 
I did not like the annoyed and cold demeanor of the staff. I felt that them limiting me to one sample was odd. However, I did not complain. When the 2nd woman came to the counter she started pointing to different entrees remarking "good!" (I guess she was helping me choose...without knowing me.), I did not complain. Even we they starting speaking in another language while serving me - clearly annoyed at the time taken by me to chose entrees off sight alone, I did not complain. All of those observations together = last visit for me. Go around the corner to Chick-fil-A, their service could make a vegetarian happy!
Great place to grab quick bite. Make sure you try the egg rolls, not filling but very tasty.

DISGUSTING!!!
We were both getting hangry, so we needed a quick bite. I regret deciding on this dump. While I was ordering, I asked if the platter came with vegetables. The woman said yes. I get to a table & open my container& there are no vegetables. My fountain soda was flat. My husband ordered peppered beef, and he said he honestly can't tell if it's fish or not.

I decided I wanted to go back to tell them how awful it was (which I did as nicely as possible), and the woman told me it wasn't peppered steak it was pork. So I'm like "Well, why does the sign say peppered steak then?" Oh, well THAT'S steak. I pay $40 for one pound for that beef. It's good beef.  

Ok, whatever, looney tune. Nobody pays $40 for a pound of crappy Chinese takeout beef. Now I'm seriously worried that we're going to get food poisoning.

reviews.text: The only reason I did 4 and not 5 is the weird pricing. Sometimes it's $9.95 and sometimes it's $10.30, but I usually always order the same thing. It's amazing though. I was a little wary at first because I thought it'd be an express kind of thing (low quality, get in get out kinda deal). Pleasantly surprised though!!! Amazing quality, very polite, and it's not super expensive! I've eaten here about 10 times already and never once was I disappointed.

I don't submit many reviews here anymore, but I feel compelled to get the word out in certain situations. And this is one of them. I'm a huge sushi fan (literally, and figuratively), and as a result I often find myself torn when looking for lunch in the Plymouth Meeting/Blue Bell area. Do I spend a lot of money (and time) going out for lunch at Bluefin or Woojung? Both are great places that deserve the praise, but I wouldn't really consider either for a quick and casual lunch during the week. As an alternative I would grab something from the to-go counter at Whole Foods, but I never felt like I was getting enough for the money in that case. Never enough freshness or flavor. Enter: Sushi Lover.

Located within the mall itself, it goes against the trend of putting new attractions outside the mall proper. It is on the lower level, between the carousel and children's play area. Local old-timers like myself might remember a snack bar located in this general spot 20+ years ago, but I digress. Anyway, from the outside it doesn't look like much...assuming you ever see it to begin with (not a lot of food traffic inside the mall these days, alas). But it solves my casual sushi dilemma perfectly. Quick, fresh, and affordable. 

Specialty rolls (like a Volcano roll) are 50% cheaper than what the other area champs would charge, and you get the benefit of something freshly prepared to order instead of sitting in a box like you would find at Whole Foods (this place is an even better deal than Whole Foods, come to think of it). They also have made-to-order smoothies and bubble teas, in a variety of flavors. Very friendly people too. The #5 combo has 6 pieces of sashimi, 4 pieces of nigiri, and an 8-piece California roll for $11.99. All prepared fresh to order (and the sashimi portions are extremely generous). No, they don't have the breadth of menu as found at the afore-mentioned spots, but that isn't what I what on a Wednesday during the one hour I can get away from the office. This place has what I want, as it has found the perfect equilibrium between my usual options for sushi goodness. Worth a visit!

I was pleasantly surprised at the quality of food considering its a little stand located on the first floor of the plymouth meeting mall.  Due to the lack of traffic in this mall, you shouldn't have to wait long.  There is a wraparound bar (minus alcohol) for you to sit and eat.

Clean, fast, courteous. 

I tried the fruit smoothie assuming it was fresh fruit and ice..it is not! Still was ok..tried the green apple but not what I expected. 

They have numerous rolls,standard and special, and plenty of beverages to choose from including bubble tea 

The Philadelphia roll was fresh and so yummy,  looking forward to trying the miso soup

reviews.text: The only Subway on the main line! The staff is well informed, but they usually tend to be college students. They made me an awesome Autumn Turkey Sandwich that was topped off with their new cranberry sauce. The location can be crowded due to it's location, but the line moves quick. It has a small TV, but the staff always knows what to play. They recently added new sliding glass over the condiments so you can easily interact with staff.

I've gotten a few sandwiches from here.  It's probably the best subway near me now, but that's because it's the only one close to me.  Sandwiches have been inconsistent.  Sometimes the ingredients seemed a little old.  This store has been out of items a few times and sometimes don't have all of the bread options.

I have been eating at Subway since I was a little I have always loved it until today I had the nastiest customer service I have ever seen. I myself have worked in the food industry and I know it is all about the customer, I felt the complete opposite. When I walked into the store there was no one at the counter and when she came she said nothing to me but looked at me, I just thought well maybe she is having a bad day and continued to tell her my order. I told her "light oil" and instead she put started to put mayo I told her "No i'm sorry I said oil." I absolutely hate mayo and she tried to argue with me and said "You said light mayo" she then took her glove inside out and started to wipe the mayo off of my sandwich it had to be the most unsanitary thing I have ever seen. I grabbed a bag of chips and put them on the counter she rang me up without asking did I want the which I did want the one with the sandwich, chips and drink she then rolled her eyes and just told me the total. I had to grab my own fountain cup and than there were no straws! I asked her for a straw and her response was her shaking her head! I was furious but I only had a 30 min lunch break, I have never been treated so rudely by someone before.

reviews.text: Great boba! I always get their ear gray milk tea with less sugar. Boba is chewy and sweet! Their strawberry smoothie was not very good - not fresh, sugary and my kids didn't even drink it! But stick to their teas and it should be good!

Just be clear with your ordering. I wanted oolong with boba and ended up getting oolong milk tea with boba ... I was told "most people order milk tea" even though I didn't.  Fortunately the person with my didn't mind a second milk tea and said it was really good.

This is one of our favorite family treats! We are almost addicted. Our favorite is the matcha and chai flavor.  We are so excited that Doylestown finally has a place that carries boba.  They also offer a convenient Door Dash option, and this was very nice on a busy day at work. I highly recommend this place!

reviews.text:
Popeye's is great fast food fried chicken and way better that KFC in our opinion. Spicy chicken, awesome biscuits, good mash potatoes. You know what your getting here if you in the mood for a greasy fast food fix. 

This review is for this location which is clean and easy to get to. The other closest Popeye's on City line ave is a parking lot nightmare and has barely no where to eat in it. This location has a nice large parking lot is very clean inside and has a pretty big eating in area.

(3.5) ~ good overall food & service.  MY WISH:  That they'd add Popeye's Sweet Potato Pies to their menu;-)

OUR MENU:
** Strawberry Fanta Soda = (4) very good
** Biscuits = (4) very good...like these better than KFC;-)
* Chicken(mild) = (3.5) good
* Chicken(spicy) = (3.5) good
* MudPie = (3.5) good

What are your EXPECTATIONS?  You're at a fast food joint so-

1. It should be fast.
2. Hopefully hot and fresh.
3. Friendly staff would be nice.
4. Clean would also be good.

Notice I didn't say low calorie!  That's the last thing you should expect here.

Generally they almost always come through on the other four.  If you like spicy, this is your place.  From the chicken to the Cajun fries, there are plenty of items that will make your tongue tingle.  The Blackened Ranch Dipping Sauce is to die for.  For about $6 you can get plenty of food and an unlimited fountain soda. The parking lot is giant so there is no problem getting in and out quickly.  

Like most places that make food in advance, it's a mistake to go here within an hour or so of closing.  When I was dumb enough to do that I was rewarded with food that had been sitting too long.  Other than that they do a solid job.

name: BAMBU
description: Desserts, Bubble Tea, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Coffee & Tea, Restaurants, Vietnamese

reviews.text:
I bought 2 items: 3 bean dessert and taro smoothie with boba. Unfortunately one was a hit, the other was horrible. Service was quick, in and out.

It is snugged away in a corner of philly in the viet area. Plenty of parking in the lot. Plenty of restaurants in the area too.

This is a chain and surprisingly similar standards and quality across the board. 

Just to reiterate, the 3 bean dessert was delicious and all the components fresh and well proportioned. Unfortunately the taro smoothie was powder and not fresh, it was sweet beyond belief and did not even taste like taro. Will not be ordering that in the future but I will be back. 

Happy eating.

I only installed yelp app to put in review for Bambu at 600 Washington Ave. The place is nothing but horrible to their customer. I ordered my drinks and they did the mistake twice, they also did it to another customer which I saw before me. Once I taste mine, it was not to my standard, my partner asked for them to make another one, a different drink and she is willing to pay the difference maybe a dollar or two, but no, the manager told her she has to pay full!!
I didn't know that she had to do this when she came back with the drink but then I saw the receipt. 

At this point I didn't event want to drink the new "dessert", I want to throw it at their faces but my partner was telling me don't do it. So, we left the place, going to the car, when I took the drink from her hand and went back with her kind of screaming behind my back scared about what I was going to do.(so I don't get arrested for destruction of property) I slammed the drink in the counter in front of the cashier and told her, "give this to your fucking manager, this is not how you do your fucking business!!" then I left.

Side note: the woman that got her drink messed up by the cashier also talk with us in the parking lot and asked us if the same thing happened and said she's so disappointed and won't come back. People who own business usually will take the loss in order to please their customers, not do things like this!

I suppose i'd give this place another try.  I didn't quite like my choice of che.  I picked the number 2: Chè thp cm (combination) - Red bean, white bean, green/mung bean, taro, pandan jelly, pearl, combo jelly.  I thought i would like this but there was just too much red and white bean and they were huge ( i should've known better).  I did like that it was not too sweet.  These type of desserts are similar to halo-halo (filipino shaved ice with toppings) but not at all as sugary.  I also tried the guy's number 4: Chè sng sáo ht lu - Grass jelly, red tapioca, pandan jelly, jello, mung bean.  Much better than mine since no red/white beans.  It would be better if they used a lid that had a bigger hole, like what dunkin donuts used for their iced drinks.  There just isn't enough room for the spoon and straw!  We came on a sunday afternoon and the place was busy but we didn't have a long wait after ordering.

reviews.text: Was a fan of Pizza Hut's pan pizza, since they closed we decided to try Dominos pan pizza. A lot better than Pizza Hut only problem they are a lot more expensive

Terrible service and unreliable staff. It took an hour and forty five minutes to deliver one pizza two miles down the road. After calling in twice and politely asking where my pizza was I was offered a free pizza. When I called in to redeem my pizza, i was told that my last order was listed as pickup, and that it was my fault it took me so long to come get it. My order was definitely delivered and definitely very late.

I want to like them because they are the closest Dominos to me but to be honest this is probably the worst Dominos I've ever had to deal with....either I've paid extra for sauces they didn't include or didn't start my pizza until I arrived or the latest one I ordered extra toppings (and paid for them) and only got it on half of the pizza?,....I am normally the give the benefit of the doubt type of person/customer but this is about the 8th time of then messing things up.....

reviews.text: This subway lacks customer service. I felt like the girl that waited on us was very rude and acted as if my daughter and I were inconveniencing her from talking to a male friend that was there keeping her company. I think I will just stick to getting my hoagies at WaWa.
Outstanding Sandwich made by Mr Patel. Good quality, friendly staff. I would definitely come back again.

I used to go to this Subway on an occasional basis to grab a quick bite for lunch or dinner.  Last November was the last time I will ever step foot back into this location.  I came in with 2 coupons.  Usually most places will run two separate charges so using 2 coupons isn't a big deal.  I ordered my sandwiches and went to checkout.  The owner refused to honor the second coupon and gave me an attitude.  Honestly, the customer service in this location sucks.  Owner also did not give me the corporate napkins too, which could possibly be a violation of their franchise agreement.  Corporate, please take note.

reviews.text: First of all let me just say, this store has a great atmosphere of healthy looking people, however I ran into an issue with the cleanliness of the store, I don't recommend sitting down and eating, if you are on a lunch break or just looking to pickup food from somewhere healthy than this is your place.

went to this location for the first time and sad to say they dont stand up to the standards of other subways i went to before.

 i ordered tuna hoagie witj extra lettuce and cheese and it was disappointing. they put a little tuna on the roll and the extra lettuce i asked for was like 10 little shreds of lettuce. there was nothing to this sandwich besides bread.

 i would not come back here ever waste of money. 

the staff were angry and looked like they didnt want to serve customers and the vibe of the place was terrible. i wont be returning.

This service at this subway is wonderful. The woman that works here is kind and goes out of her way to please the customer. It is subway so the sandwiches are the same but service is key. It is also the cleanest subway I have ever been in. As I was leaving the gentleman working was on his knees cleaning the legs of the table that people rest their feet on. They wipe down everything and are a great franchise representative of Subway corporation. If you are out shopping and want to grab an inexpensive bite to eat I highly recommend this location.

reviews.text: If you don't like seafood, this is a waste of money. Very little choices in general, but desserts were dry, all sauces tasted watered down, and only had two choices of chicken. Don't waste your money, go somewhere else.

For a buffet located in a Wal-Mart shopping center in Pottstown this wasn't bad. Ate here years ago and was disappointed but this recent trip was not too shabby. The generals chicken had flavor and a mild spice. The pork bun was a pleasant surprise.  The wife enjoyed the coconut shrimp. My daughter, who is vegetarian went up three times. There was an older man who watched the food and kept it filled and the tables clean at the buffet. If you want high class chinese food don't eat here. But for what it is.. it's a 4 star delight.
Best and cheapest Chinese buffet. The food isn't phenomenal but sure beats other Chinese restaurants for a fraction of the cost

reviews.text: Was duped earlier by a restaurant down the that lied about their closing hours and was in a pinch. Drove past here saw it was opened even though it was nearing 11. Hated to do it if they were going to close but owner was very friendly and wanted my business. Food was great, def my new go to.

The food is so-so.  The man who works there is rude and does not listen.  I told him I was going to pay for an order that someone else was picking up.  First, he hung up on me.  Then, when I called back, he was very rude and going on and on about something.  I asked if he'd like me to call another restaurant.  I cancelled my order. I will never order from this restaurant again.  There are much better places in the area.  Joe's Peking is so much better.

Given the options in the area for chinese fast food, this place is pretty good. Their sauteed string beans are hit or miss depending on the time of season or more specifically the freshness of the beans they have to work with. Their lo mein noodles are just okay. Their rice is kind of dry and tasteless. Their orange chicken is pretty good and consistent.

reviews.text: Service is great- quality of food is horrible! We ordered some chicken wings which were $4.50- got 3 tiny drumsticks and 3 sad wingettes. Definitely not worth the cost! We also ordered 2 shrimp rolls- they were extremely hard on the outside and the insides were full of grease, I understand they were fried but they were oozing the grease they were fried in. The shrimp fried rice was tasteless. Over all spent $20 and wish I hadn't. Will not be ordering or taking out anything from this place. Such a shame because the staff was so pleasant.

Food was tasteless we had chicken and Chinese vegetables and sesame chicken sesame chicken place at best OK The chicken and Chinese vegetables was tasteless seemed like it had no seasoning very little taste The lo mein was very tasteless I can't even imagine how it could have no taste like that like they had no seasoning new salt not but it looked good

Good food made quick. I can always rely on the chicken with broccoli to be delicious. Crab Rangoon, fried dumplings and fried wontons are usually always good options. Orange chicken and general tso's are my wife's go tos. Only had greasy eggrolls once or twice in the past 4 years but still worth the 5 stars. Took my son in with me tonight and they gave us a fresh cut up watermelon for him! Always great customer service!

This is the first stop I make whenever I come to King of Prussia and YES, I live in NYC- the land of pizza.  The pizza is the best I've experienced.  It has an excellent sauce (properly seasoned) to cheese ratio and the crust is always the right consistency.

The price is right and as an added bonus you have the owner, Tony, who is the nicest guy you could ever meet. He is always giving back to the community and therefore the community should take care of him.

Great food, even better service! From out of town and definitley will be back. 

Didn't know it was cash only, owner said just pay me next time. Explained I was from out of town, he said you'll be back at some point. 

Got cash out from ATM in back of shop, but excellent service. Definitley creates a culture of trust with the customer.

I was a little disappointed - I was there for a business dinner and my guest ordered the cooked tuna steak - which he said was off - so he didn't touch it - the server asked how things were, we were honest...sushi good (not great) but we weren't taking chances - she said, oh, can I get you something else - so he ordered a single sushi order - when the bill came - both were on the bill.  So, I've had better - service and sushi...

Quite possibly the best shrimp tempura rolls I've ever eaten. Looking forward to being back in the area so I can go again!! Lunchtime was pretty slow, our service was quick. Also tried the hibachi noodles and they were very good. Great spot in Deptford

description: Coffee & Tea, Beauty & Spas, Cosmetics & Beauty Supply, Shopping, Arts & Crafts, Costumes, Restaurants, Vietnamese, Food

reviews.text:
Ah, it's hard to go wrong with pho and this place is no exception! Our server was attentive and our food came out quickly. The restaurant was decently packed by not overflowing with people; we came for brunch/lunch hour. A great bowl of pho for a great price! Will be back again.

Note: $15 minimum, bring cash.

I think i could go here every day for lunch if left to my own devices.
What's not to like
-avail parking
-great food
-and easy to get to from i95

I wanted to stretch my legs after being snowed in and left home in search of food and beer.  Instead of going to my usual Vietnamese place, I tried Pho Saigon since I was at the distributor next door.  I ordered the chicken vermicelli with a spring roll.  The only good thing I can is that the vermicelli is very good.  The spring roll was burnt and greasy.  I took one bite and threw it out.  The chicken came with the skin on, which I don't prefer.  I would have been willing to overlook it, but like the spring roll, it was also very greasy.  I might give this place another shot to try out the pho, but otherwise I won't be back.

reviews.text: Staff were super nice.  I was welcomed at the door. And after I made my order I realized I couldn't eat the salad bc of a dietary issue and they exchanged it for a soup with no problem.  I will be back the next time I'm in this complex. Food was fresh and delicious!

Let me just say I LOVE Panera bread. This location though is absolutely horrible. I've ordered many times food from them. I ordered my lunch as usual, now it was delivered but it was missing the main part the SOUP. Which isn't a big deal i thought, well apparently after speaking with "Summer" was told that they do not deliver nor do they give refunds. I asked to speak to a manager AARON hoping i could actually get my lunch. Aaron was very rude and condescending. He did not apologize and tried to shift the blame on the delivery service door dash. I spend a lot of money eating there and this is the last time i will EVER support this location. After about 20 minutes of holding passing me back and forth btw summer and this manger Aaron They issued me a refund of 2 dollars for the missing soup. Disgraceful! They should have refunded the whole bill amount or try to fix the situation. Which they refused to deliver my soup, so i had to leave work and go get food some where else. So much for loyal customers, loyalty is not something Panera specializes in.  Very very disappointed

The best Panera I have ever been too. Such good atmosphere and the employees are so friendly and helpful. I saw one of the managers help an elder lady transfer her hot drink into her own travel mug. I came during lunch hour (which is their busiest time) and  the food came out fast and delicious. All my orders were correct and my latte tasted as good as I would expect it. I can't say that about any other Panera that have been too.

reviews.text: I visited this place when they first opened and have been back many times! Their food is delicious and the service is great. They're very friendly and want to make sure you enjoy what you've ordered. They have an excellent variety of tasty dishes ranging from Mediterranean, Indian, to cheese steaks. It's a perfect place to grab food any night of the week!
My 2nd time here and they do not disappoint! Their wings and gyros are awesome! Look outside the box and give them a chance everything is fresh! I watched them cook they go above and beyond.
Great service and delicious food! Ordered the Combo Platter with Rice and Salad. Would recommend stopping by here for sure.

reviews.text: Could have been better. Unlike Chinese food at all. No taste soever. Seems like Depending on a persons personality, they serve the quantity and not evenly for everyone.
Eh. I know you can't expect much from mall food court fare but I will say the chicken had a nice char and the noodles were pretty yummy, albeit oily. The egg roll was also pretty decent.

For being mall chinese food, I actually really like this place. I'll usually go there if I have to go there to shop and the food is very consistent and has good flavor. Everything I've had from them I've like. 

Love their vegetable fried rice and vegetable Lo mein. The counter women and cashiers are always very friendly.

name: Kung Fu Tea
description: Taiwanese, Food, Bubble Tea, Juice Bars & Smoothies, Restaurants, Coffee & Tea

reviews.text: I am a door dasher and today I picked up an order to deliver from this location. the tea leaked........BADLY on my way to the customer's house. I came back to Kung Fu to get a new one. They REFUSED to make the customer a new one! Wouldn't help me at all! I've worked in the restaurant industry for many years at several different restaurants. Every time there was something wrong with a customer's order or something happened to it, the restaurant would always make a new one whether it was their fault or not. Terrible customer service! I will also be complaining to Door Dash about them.

Brand new bubble tea in the area, clean facility, and good service. Love the popcorn chicken and the honey milk tea; altho the sauce for the pop corn chicken was too little and the rice to avocado ratio for the avocado kani was very little avocado filling and a bit more on the rice side. It still taste good tho. Would definitely come back again.

It takes unique taste buds to enjoy this cold milk bubble tea. It caught me off guard. It reminded me of instant tea we had in the 70s mixed with milk. Then you get surprises with large pieces of tapioca that taste like tea flavored gummies.

I'll come back to try same flavor but HOT. I'm not knocking this. It's worth the experience.

name: Panera Bread
address: 2010 Marlton Pike W, Bldg F - Ste A
description: Bagels, Bakeries, Food, Salad, Sandwiches, Breakfast & Brunch, Soup, Restaurants

reviews.text: I visited this Panera Bread yesterday and Ordered a Chicken Caesar Sandwich with no tomatoes and I asked for red onions . I watched the manager tell the young guy  how to make my sandwich . Once i got the sandwich I opened it right away just to check it before leaving , I had bread grilled chicken and lots of Parmesan cheese no lettuce , no Caesar no onions . I told the manager he said he would make me another right away  which he made me ( and I didn't check ) got home and it was also completely wrong but It was  better but wrong . I won't be visiting  that location anymore. Panera Bread is to expensive for my food not to right .

I like it all. 
I noticed I go to this Panera a lot, mostly for it's super convenient location. Parking in the back isn't great but you'll eventually find something. 

Some of my favorites are the Napa Almond Chicken Salad Sandwich, French Onion soup and the coffee cake ring. Who am I trying to kid? I love all pastries. Newly discovered favorite side dish, the mac & cheese. Tastes like Stouffers from back in the day; it's creamy & delicious.

Their baguettes are fantastic, but I usually get the apple as my side and going to say, you need to do better on finding these apples. I love the size, but sometimes they are mealy. Get a good, crisp, mini apple and you've got a customer for life.

When it's busy, I get it, but I personally haven't had a moment where I'm fuming mad. Get some lemonade and patiently wait for your tasty meal to be ready.
Good food, adore the tea but the music was so bad I was longing for an icepick to stab out my ears.

reviews.text: This place has pretty good pho, broken rice, and ice coffee. The only down side is I wish there were more food options on the menu. Otherwise, I am satisfied with the food and the drink.
I had great service here! The workers were sooo so nice, the pho's good and the portions were huge!!

It's your typical pho joint, not the best but good enough if you're craving something Viet. I haven't explored most of the pho options in the city, but compared to all of the pho I've had in my life, it wasn't anything special.

We ordered the banh uot cha lua with nem (folded rice noodles/crepes with Viet cold cuts), pho dac biet, and bun mam. Banh uot was solid, though to be fair, there's not much cooking involved. The pho was missing some depth to its flavor and the broth could have been a bit clearer. I was also disappointed that there wasn't any tripe in the pho either. The bun mam was flavorful but a bit greasy with a thick layer of oil on top.

Portions are good though and service is nice. Just remember to pay at the counter after you're finished with your meal.

reviews.text: They came back!  Ordered on New Years bcs I missed their lava cakes, and it was actually good quality.  The delivery was quick, and the pizza was fresh.  Hopefully this means these problems are fixed for good!

I usually try to go the non-chain route when it comes to pizza.  However, when I am looking for a speedy delivery and can knock out a quick order online, Domino's fits the bill just fine.  As far as quality goes my family likes their new handmade pan style pizza.  I also like that they have garlic sauce available as a side.  

My experiences here have always been positive whether it be delivery or carry-out.

First off -- it's Domino's.  What I mean by that is that it's chain-store pizza and for what it is, it's pretty decent.  Domino's really can't compete with quality local pizza, but unfortunately in this area, that's slim pickings around here!  In terms of taste and quality, I think Domino's food is better than their chain-pizza competitors.

Per this particular location, the food is often prepared in a timely manner, the people are usually nice when I go in to pick it up and everything has turned out as expected.

As for the pizza, I've never been a big fan of Domino's red sauce since they changed it a few years back, but you can't help but love the garlic crust that also came about when they were making pizza taste changes.  My personal favorite Domino's pizzas to order are a white pizza with bacon and their BBQ chicken pizza.

I haven't had too many other non-pizza offerings, but the chicken parm sandwich is pretty tasty and I've always been a fan of their cheesy bread.  The only other thing I've had is their boneless chicken and that definitely wasn't worth the money for the amount you get.

Overall -- it's Domino's and for a Domino's this is a good Domino's. If you like chain pizza, this location is a good one to get your food from.

reviews.text:
Couldn't find a menu online. Called and asked if they had one and was told no. Then they hung up. I had 30 crew members to feed and now I'm looking for somewhere else. 

How many orders do you think this business misses because it doesn't have a menu online? 

I guess this is what you get when you're in South Jersey.

While visiting my home town I decided to pick up some chinese. Food was decent. Still hot once I got it home. Prices were good. The place looks pretty dingy, definitely not the type of spot to sit in and eat.
I needed/wanted soup today and options were scarce. I got wonton soup and chicken with broccoli. This is some of the best Chinese food around here. Great service, great prices and great food

reviews.text:
The pho here is great.  The broth is really flavorful, they give you plenty of meat, it's cheap and the portions are HUGE.

The only downfalls- The place smelled like a dirty rag and although I don't ever expect frequent water refills or even water at all at a pho place, I at least expect it if I ask for it.  I asked the one waiter and he walked 2 feet to the counter and forgot.  He ended up chatting with someone then walking back to clear tables.  I had to go to the counter and get it myself.

Good stuff, good stuff. Soup flavor is consistently good. Service is very in and out: just sit, order, eat and go. Average price. Very clean. Plenty of parking in lot where you don't have to fight ppl nor traffic in Chinatown. Located next to an Asian supermarket. I can see why my friend swears by this place. 

Beef pho, good
Chicken pho, good
Vermicelli, good
Summer rolls, good
Coffee, good
Egg rolls, only thing that could use work
Very clean and nice. Great price. Nice waitstaff, and has a takeout menu. Food was AMAZING

name: Subway
address: 501 S Broad St, Ste 13, The Pavillion

reviews.text: The workers there were rude and were more worried about their own conversation rather to help me out. Do not get fountain sodas from there, the ice maker is filthy, full of dirt. I tried 3 times getting ice from ice dispenser and all 3 times I had something in the ice. Disgusting. I would never go back, Period.

I had a great experience here. I got the cali sub and it was delicous. A nice young man works there...wish I would have got his name. Kudos to him for having great customer service skills and a good personality. Will go agian.

I can't really rate anything besides false hours. I showed up on Saturday night around 840 and the doors were locked. The signs clearly said open but the crew could be seen cleaning up for the night. What are the hours of operations? Even on yelp it has you open til 9pm... Your lose was someone elses gain. The pizza steak at Palermos across the parking lot was amazing.

reviews.text:
Quick and courteous service. Convenience store is attached with a nice sitting area with a large TV with the local sports team game on if there is a game on.

The convenience store also serves La Colombe coffee in the morning, and have cold brew coffee available as well in the cooler.

I was in the Fort Washington area for a brunch after a wedding. Since I was a bit hungry, I decided to stop off at this Subway for lunch. 

I came in and was warmly greeted by the singe staff member. 

I decided to try their seasonal, autumn carved turkey sandwich. I got my sandwich on honey oat bread with cheddar cheese. 

While my sandwich was in the oven being toasted, I watched the Eagles on their TV in their small lounge section. 

After that, I picked out my toppings, which the staff member helped me choose. Finally, I got two chocolate chip cookies! 

My sandwich was absolutely delicious and fresh! I especially loved the cranberry mustard sauce on top! 

As I stated before, the staff was very nice here. He really went above and beyond! 

Altogether, I had a great experience at this Subway!

I stopped into this subway for lunch.  Wow!  It was great.  Excellent food and service.  They have a small lounge with a large tv.  Bathroom was spotless and welcoming.  I got two free cookies - probably because I brought my whole family - all 7 of us.  Cost over $60 but worth every penny. We had a really great lunch and enjoyed watching the eagles game at the same time.  Will definitely come back.  Great owner - friendly and knows sports pretty good, but not great.Gary really is terrific.

name: Panera Bread
description: Bakeries, Food, Salad, Restaurants, Cafes, Sandwiches, Soup

reviews.text:
0/10 avoid this location at all costs

Service:
Everyone working here makes it blatantly obvious that they hate their jobs. One girl was lazy af! My total for coffee came out to be like $2.12 or something so I gave her a $5 and 12 pennies, and she stared at me like "are you really gonna make me count these?"

Food:
Below average, especially for the price. Pasta primavera tasted and smelled like microwaved vegetables. My boyfriend got soup and a panini, both were salty and nothing special. Iced coffee was extremely watered down.

Just don't even waste your time, trust me.

Everyone needs a friendly reliable breakfast and quick lunch place. Unfortunately, this Panera always disappoints. The workers are miserable. We were  here today at 7:10 am, and as is the norm, they had no more souffles.  I asked how they are out of souffles this early in the day. The surly person at the counter was clearly annoyed and rudely said "they're in the oven and it will take 20 minutes!" It would have been helpful to know that when I first inquired.
This is this place's mo-jo. I am tempted to sit down with the manager and ask if they keep inventory of how many souffles they sell per 1/2 hour in the morning. It should be predictable - they should never be out of souffles. The staff clearly needs more customer service training.
So don't waste your time here. Pick a friendly neighborhood diner instead.

Unfortunately I've become an ex-Panera Bread customer due to an incident that happened in January of this year. In preparation for the predicted blizzard, my wife was out running some errands and called me asking if I wanted her to pick up something for lunch while she was still out. I suggested that I place an order with Panera using the phone app that I had used many times before and she could just walk in and pick it up without a hassle since payment happens at the time of order. As an after thought, I put two cookies on the order prior to final submission and scheduled it for 11:30 pick up. After fighting considerable problems finding a place to park in the shopping center due to traffic caused by the upcoming snow, she ran in and took the bag with our order from the pick up shelf and headed home. Upon arriving home, we opened the bag and discovered that the two cookies had not been placed in the bag even though I had been billed for them. I immediately called the restaurant and spoke to a girl who obviously could care less and was just in a hurry to get me off the phone. She said if I came back down, I could pick up the cookies. I stated that due to the traffic situation, I would just like a credit written on my Amex card for the two cookies at $1.99 each. She said the manager would have to do that procedure and he wasn't available. I gave her my order number, phone number, etc. and told her to have someone call if there was a problem. I waited until the following week and the credit had not shown up on my card. Frustrated, I went to the Panera website and detailed my problem as stated above. I left all my contact information, etc. NO ONE BOTHERED REPLYING TO MY EMAIL COMPLAINT! So, for the lack of response over two cookies, Panera has lost a loyal customer. I will not return to any Panera location based on their terrible lack of customer service. Although I will certainly miss the cinnamon crunch bagels, I can't return to a business that treats customers in this manner.

reviews.text: Came here on a Sunday afternoon for lunch with hubby. He ordered the pork chop rice. I asked the waiter what one of the photo I pointed to was and he said " mango chicken salad". I said ok, I'll try it but I specifically asked if they put peanuts on it, he said no, but just in case I asked him to please make sure there's no peanuts. Many Vietnamese dishes love to top their dishes with peanuts. Hubby got his dish and he said it was average. Few minutes after he got his, I got my mango salad, with peanuts . They took it back and made another one. The mango had a nice crunch to it. After about my 3rd piece I realize, there was no chicken. I asked my hubby if I heard it wrong and he agreed that the waiter did mention there was chicken in it. I didn't want to send it back again. I just ate the mango dish and left it at that. Between the mango salad (which is quite a small dish) and his pork chop rice with viet coffee, it cost close to $30. Maybe the waiter didn't familiarize all the dishes yet. But I can give it another try for their hot pot next time :) as for their dishes, in my opinion, it tasted like any viet dish I've had around.
Good food, good price!!! I live in jersey city but Everytime I come to Phila to do something, this is always the place that I stop to eat, either breakfast or dinner!

Beware they sell dead clams !!! I got clams with tamarind sauce to go and when I get home this is what I saw, all the clams are not open cause they're dead. They can't not charging people $20 for dead clams !!! I will not come here again

reviews.text: We brought some of my daughters friends here for dinner to celebrate her birthday. We chose it specifically because they offer gluten free rolls. We all thoroughly enjoyed our sandwiches. Not what you would refer to as a typically Philly cheesesteak but still tasty. The gluten free sandwich took some extra time to come out but they explained that it was because they had to take the time to clean the grill. That made us feel much better that they understand what it means to be gluten free! We will definitely return.

We are always on the lookout for a quality sandwich place near our home. This would have been really convenient, and we'd have been overjoyed to like this place. Unfortunately, we were really disappointed.

We got regular size hoagies that look nothing like the photo they show on their website. They said one sandwich would "feed 2 people" for almost $10 with tax. What 2 people do you know who will eat 3.5" of sandwich for a meal and be satisfied? Not two grown-adult non-anorexic Philadelphians. Was this a mistake by a new employee or something?

This place is new, and I try to pad reviews for newer places even when I don't dig them, but in this case, I could not finish eating my meal, so I can't ignore that.

Just under $19 for two 7" hoagies that were Wawa quality, from roll, to meats, to mayo.

In fairness, I am not a chain hoagie person. If you like places like Primo's, Subway or Wawa, then by all means, help yourself to Jersey Mike's. But if you are more of a mom-n-pop authentic Philly sandwich type of person, who has come to know the quality meats, toppings and rolls that our area has to offer, then I don't think the quality at this place will stand up to what you're used to.

We had a turkey hoagie and an Italian, both were very low-quality meats. Also, the veggies were tasteless and the roll was terrible. It was definitely the kind of roll you'd get at Subway, not at all something that tasted fresh from a Philly bakery.

My turkey was the same rubbery-looking stuff they give you at Wawa. I could not finish. Wasted half the sandwich, which was only 7 measly inches to begin with.

The Italian was no better. Not much flavor, all lower-quality ingredients. Thinly-packed, with not much in it at all. Again, very disappointing.

They put a lot of hype into their marketing and advertising, and have fancy logo-printed wax paper and bags. The bag and wax paper presentation was like Burger King. Please, save the money on the logos and put it into better quality ingredients. To us, you just branded something we will never eat again, and couldn't finish. Wasted money. Had to go out again to get takeout elsewhere just to finish dinner.

Sorry Jersey Mike's, we heard great things about you on Philly.com and thought you'd be different from Primo's. I guess a franchise, is a franchise, is a franchise. It's just not for us.

reviews.text: They use gloves to make your sandwiches but the guy who made mine had his on when I walked in and he was in the lobby.   He walked behind the counter, using his gloved hands to touch all surfaces and wiped his shirt and adjusted his clothes all with the gloves he then used to make my food.   It was kind of disgusting.

The service was horrible. Snippy staff, no greeting, acted like they wanted to be anywhere but there working. Took 25 min to checkout and we were third in line. Product was good but service and timing was horrible. Not going back.

Hello again, I'm here this time to review Jersey Mike's. When we walked in we was immediately greeted gold star for that. They took our order promptly, Another gold star! Oh any Veterans they have military discount there. When we sat in our car to eat my wife showed me her cheesesteak sandwich, it looked like the gold doors opened and a bright light came out and the angels were singing, I mean this sandwich looked BEAUTIFUL! and my wife eat it and it tasted even better, a work of art. So my wife went back in to compliment the cook by the way her name is Sara, and she told my wife that she was a chef but lost her job because of covid 19. SUPERB! So if any restaurants is looking for a great chef her name is Sara. And now my score.........
1000 points!!!

reviews.text: I came here because people at school told me that this place is amazing, but it's not even close to amazing. The sushi was okay. It was not the best sushi I've had. The sushi was pretty expensive and the pieces were extra small compared to other sushi restaurants. I ordered the sashimi lunch special and it didn't taste that fresh. I wouldn't come here again for sushi but the customer service was good.

The sushi is insanely cheap but it does come with a trade off with quality. I do come here often because it's close. A lot of the rolls are fried but honestly i don't know if I would trust the sashimi here. It's not terrible, but not impressive either.

Great sushi at an even better price! The pink lady was phenomenal. Grilled calamari was excellent and was a very different take on it. Service was perfect, everything was from deinks to desert were all right on time. Fish was very fresh.

reviews.text: Great food at a decent price. Very quick and efficient with both delivery and take out. It's always been nice and freshly cooked.  You can also order online which we really like. Very user friendly site. Staff is always kind too. We love their sweet and sour chicken, dumplings, teriyaki chicken and rice noodles! Definitely recommend this place!!

online delivery was QUICK on a Sunday night (30 minutes from order to door)  -  the convenience of ordering online was great. The only thing was for a custom order they didn't pay attention to the notes I included about no spicy peppers or white rice instead of fried rice. Food tasted yummy.

Ordered Chinese food from my go to Golden Key added in the tip to my phone order. The driver came to the door in a Santa suit I hobbled to the door after recent foot surgery signed for my order said Merry Christmas to the driver and got a silent stare in return. Went inside and realized they didn't include my tip on the receipt. Called to tell them but still feeling very unsettled by the interaction.

reviews.text:
It's a Subway, so you know the drill. I'm only docking stars for this location on account of its overall atmosphere and the service. Aside from that, the sandwiches are exactly the same as at every other Subway on the planet.

Also, they haven't kicked on the A/C yet. I mean, I know it costs money, but seriously. It's like 90 degrees out.

Ordered a sandwich for pickup via a living social "deal" that was $4 for a footlong combo.  Sandwich was ready timely upon pickup.  I order a turkey sub with 4 free toppings and avocado.  As I open the sandwich in my office, one topping and the avocado (which I paid extra for) was missing.   Awful service.  Can't get a printed order correct.

My husband and I take turns stopping in on the weekends for their egg flatbreads. They guy who works in the morning on the weekend is great -- friendly, efficient, and remembered us and our orders after a couple visits.

reviews.text:
I had a 6 inch tuna fish sandwich with cheese potato chips and a drink for lunch. The staff was friendly. I received my food fairly quickly, and the price of $8 was very reasonable.  The food was delicious and I enjoyed it. 

There is a large parking lot in front of the store, which is located on a corner of an intersection.  The subway store was clean.

I just returned from this store and here is my experiece. 1) The chicken is not fresh and I could not eat a 6" sub and had to throw it away. 2) Noticed that they put lot lettuce but very less of other items 3) The meat in the containers look dried as if they put that 2 days back. 

Not worthy to go.

Typical Subway....

Good food that you decide what you want on it and how you like it from the roll on. The service has been decent for the most part every time I've come here. Seem to be a slower overall then other subways I've gone to in the area.

Personally I go for the chicken teriyaki sandwich with extra meat, lettuce and onions. Service has been hit and miss. Sometimes the lettuce and onions don't look particular fresh though and I wish the manager would work to make this place better.

Overall you get a good sandwich with or without the extra meat for a decent price just expect to get it slower then other locations.

name: Subway
description: Fast Food, Sandwiches, Restaurants, Salad, American (Traditional)

reviews.text: Very Clean, spacious.  If you like subway, the hoagies won't disappoint.  The staff was very nice.  I had someone new serve me, and she couldn't have been nicer.
Went to Subway to order a sandwich and they're closed before 10pm. The restaurant was clean as if they closed hours ago. I'm calling corporate in the morning.

If I could give this place 0 stars I would. Lazy establishment, don't answer calls. Hours aren't what they say they are. Do not recommend going to this subway unless you're looking for a waste of your time.

name: Mr. Wish
description: Taiwanese, Bubble Tea, Food, Restaurants, Juice Bars & Smoothies

reviews.text:
It was our first time at Mr. Wish and it was really good! The service was fast, and the employees were helpful and of course what my sister and I got both was really tasty and refreshing. We told them it was our first time, and they said they use all fresh fruit and everything they have is refreshing. 

I got a mango smoothie, which only comes in a medium size and it had small chunks of frozen mango. The medium was a good size but it was $4.75, which is a bit expensive. 

My sister got the mango tea with fresh pulp in the large size. She asked for boba pearls which was 75¢ extra for the topping, so hers ended up being $6.25 but the large is a good size. My sister says it was very fresh. 

Inside the actual store front it was a good size, not too big and not too small. It had some tables and chairs to wait or sit and eat in. I was able to pay with my card, and tip on their iPad and text the receipt to my phone easy peasy. Overall I would go back again,   especially because the location was close to my house. There are also a lot of other locations near my house, which speaks to their popularity in the area. 10/10

Sure you may have to wait a little longer when it's busy, but the drinks are worth it. Probably the best Mr. Wish I've been to actually. The Mango smoothie is made with care and you can actually taste the fresh mango. Plus the staff is pleasant, which makes a world of difference too. I'm sure they will grow their staff with time since they just opened.
Came here a few times already. They're consistent, friendly, and just what you'd expect from a bubble tea spot. Great environment, clean establishment, can't go wrong.

I love that they include blue cheese and celery some places I've been to charge extra for it. Can't say much about the rest of the menu because I only get their wings

Going to grandmom's house for pizza so we thought what would be better than picking up some wings.  Great place! Prices are reasonable.  Great selection of sauces.  We got mild and honey bbq.  Next time hubby wants them a little hotter.  I am cool with just mild!!!   

The guy who works there was really nice and friendly. We called in our order and they were waiting when we got there.

reviews.text: First time here, tonight(3/17/13).  Sister lives nearby and wanted to come here for dinner. We are both vegetarians, so I ordered the Gen. Tsos Bean Curds because she said it was good, n boy was she right! The tofu was nice n crisp outside, and not mushy. The sauce was sweet n spicy, just right. The food was piping hot. My nephew ate honey chicken with pork fried rice, but i couldn't see the pork, LOL. He said the chicken was really good, n his eggroll likewise. I also had hot n sour soup, which was delicious as not many places can make it good. I ordered a scallion pancake which my SIS liked, but i thought was just a Lil too doughy for me, but dipping sauce was good. SIS n i both had springrolls, n she devoured hers, n i will eat mine with my leftovers. N this establishment happens to have brown rice, which I prefer over white rice. Overall, I was pleased n impressed, as initial impression was...I sure hope their food is good. I will definitely be back, n i added them to yelp so others can enjoy their food too!!!!

name: Red Mango
description: Juice Bars & Smoothies, Food, Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt

reviews.text:
Philly is home to many frozen yogurt shops including Sweet Ending and Yogorino. Red Mango certainly gets the job done as well.

They have more than a few self-serve ptions - with the majority being fruit-flavored, including White Peach and Mandarin Orange.

As with most froyo joints, you've got a wide variety of fruit, candy, and chocolate toppings. 

Red Mango Frozen Yogurt ($0.49/oz)

The GF opted for the classic with a medley of fruit and granola. The yogurt was tart and the fruit was ripe - nothing wrong here!

Red Mango will get the job done if you're craving some froyo. Still, Philly has plenty of froyo joints and I don't really see how Red Mango separates itself from the rest of the crowd.
Pomegranate smoothie = refreshing and delicious. Chocolate sorbetto = caused major GI issues for my friend and I. I will stick with the smoothies here.

So, I love decorating with red and enjoyed the decor. The name says it all, plus the mango... if you like fruit choices like I do. This is the spot. Fruit is fresh and cut to just the right size.

I love this area, good for walking the street and watching people walk around. I've only been here 3 times, but this place is always clean.

reviews.text:
My partner likes cinnamon rolls. I do not. If I'm being overdramatic, this was one of the biggest conflicts in our relationship. 

But then we discovered the sticky buns from Wild Flour Bakery at the Collingswood Market. Wow-za! Aside from the cinnamon, I don't know what the difference between sticky buns and cinnamon rolls is, but these sticky buns do it for BOTH of us. I'm glad there's now a cinnamon roll-like treat that we can both enjoy! 

And of course, everything else we got was incredible too. I'm really glad we got to give this place a chance while the market was open this year and I can't wait for it to reopen next year!

Two words: BEER BREAD.  There are 2 varieties of beer bread made here, and they are both amazing. I don't eat much bread, but if you live alone I recommend sharing a loaf with a friend or freezing the rest, as it freezes well. This is only one of 2 bakeries from which I will eat the bread. The offerings are outstanding. DO YOU HEAR ME????!!! I said out STANDing, fools. 
          The other things - flatbreads, pastries, and weekly whims of fancy (they dig getting creative, so don't get addicted to a special SPECIAL item, cause it may not be there next time) - all rise above thebar, and ever you find the crew at a Farmers Market, you can bet that one of the baker dudes is there and will proudly answer all of your questions. 
           When it comes to coffee or bread, nothing but the very best cross my lips. I deserve that - and so do you. Treat thyself!

Sorry to be writing this...

So I got baguette #2 from the Rittenhouse Square market this past weekend. I hate to say it, because I have only the best feeling about this bakery, but it wasn't up to par this time. Here's the reason why: there was NO salt in the baguette (I mean none at all.) I'm assuming this was a mistake that the baker made - someone just forgot to add the salt in one batch. It happens. The bread was still okay, but a baguette without salt just tastes really lacking. I can get past it for Tuscan bread or a soft pretzel, but for this loaf, I just couldn't get past it. 
I will definitely be trying again next week and hopefully I will get another stellar loaf like the previous one I had. I also can't wait to try their croissants and brioche loaf! So I will try them again soon and re-update this, hopefully with better news!

reviews.text: The friendliness of the employees isnt too bad but the fact that the don't accept any Subway coupons and they are frequently out of the most basic hoagie ingredients (how can a hoagie shop be out of ham?!?!?) is a deal breaker for me.

Absolutely terrible!  Should be 0 stars or less.  Single employee running this Subway at the Plymouth Meeting Mall was incompetent, incapable and an idiot at lunchtime on 7/14/21.  I ordered a 6" turkey with American cheese and a little Mayo.  He maimed the bread cutting it incompletely and then 'finished' the job ripping it open with his hands.  Threw the turkey & cheese on the bread and then squeezed a huge amount of Mayo on it.  I also ordered 2 plain soft pretzels and repeatedly told him no cinnamon.  As you might guess the pretzels had cinnamon on them.  He moved at glacial speed.  Why I paid for this slop is beyond me.

If you go to the plymouth meeting mall don't go to this subway. First of all none of the employees know what good costumer service means. Another problem is that they never participate with any of the subway offers. If that wasn't enough you can usually see mosquitoes flying around the fresh ingredients

reviews.text: Yummy Cheesy Pizza! If you like soft doughy pizza with lots of cheese order from here. I've never been to the restaurant but have had delivery several times.  Never had any issues with wrong orders or bad food.

Positives - In my opinion, they've got really good pizza. No, nothing is mind blowing, but more than solid and nothing to complain about. Granted I don't come here very often, but I've never experienced anything subpar or awful.

The Buffalo tails are off the hook. Great buffalo sauce that's slightly sweet, but balanced out by a little heat.

Negatives - Again, I don't come here often, but I've never had anything bad. The pizza fries weren't very good and lacked sauce and cheese, but it wasn't a deal breaker.

The customer service was fine to me, but I could see how they could possibly rub some people the wrong way.

While the food is slightly above average, the customer service is extremely poor. The person answering the phone is not helpful, not courteous and completely unprofessional. With all the pizza places around I will NEVER go here again.

reviews.text:
After reading the previous reviews on Yelp, I decided to give this place a try - specifically, the Singapore Mei Fun lol. 

I remember one time I ordered pork chops with rice at a food truck and was greeted with fried chicken wings, rice, and some bitter broccoli when I got back - FAIL.  So of course, I came to this place with big hopes but little expectations.  

Now, let me just say hat this was one of the best food stands/trucks type around Temple that I have ever encountered. 

I was totally surprised by the amount of chicken, roasted pork, and shrimp in the serving!  Trust me, it's not just a deceiving few laid on top, and you'll never have to dig through it to find some meat.  With that said, I thought the chicken was a little dry...but the pork and shrimp made up for it and the portions were definitely generous for only $5.50!!!!  I haven't tried its other dishes but I can testify that the Singapore Mei Fun is well worth the price. 

Also the food comes in a decent sized aluminum plate with a plastic cover, which I think is much more convenient and healthy than the cheap styrofoam lunch boxes.  And instead of a plastic bag, you'll get a paper lunch bag, yay! 

Anyway, the service is fast and efficient; I went a little past 1 and there was not much of a line when I got there.  If you're unsure about what to order, try the mei fun!

Oh, and the guy indeed yells SING MEI in a very cool manner.  :)

Food is always great. Hot and sour soup there is a lot different than other places. Tastes really good. It's Chinese food (duh!) so expect it to have grease. I can assure that all Chinese food has grease, so I don't know what the complaint is about grease... anyways I think it's less greasier than your average Chinese food in the corner.

Food is always greasy, American Chinese dishes. The owners also decided to negatively critique my physical appearance in front of my face thinking that I don't understand. Very rude. Would never shop here again.

reviews.text: Obviously if you have eaten at subway before the food is the same at every location the difference is the staff.  This subway is HORRIBLE for service.  They have two girls that work there that are friendly and polite.  Every other girl they have working there is just down right rude.  One girl even tries to put less meat on your sandwich if she thinks you are not looking.  They act like it is an inconvenience if you have to ask them what kind of soup they have but you always have to ask because they never update the board that tells you.  I, unfortunatly, am stuck going to this location if I want subway for lunch because I only have a short lunch break and this is the only location that I am able to make it to in my time frame.  If you are able to avoid this subway I would definatly reccomend finding a different location.

Subway is the only 'fast food' I eat, and this location is probably my favorite in the city.  The bread is always fresh.  One the best parts about this place is that they always have plenty veggie patties on hand, which for a vegetarian, is a nice option.

I got a footlong Veggie Delite yesterday and it was a good, cheap dinner.  The components were decent for what they were, albeit none of high quality or in their prime.  The hoagie was well made with the right amounts of oil and vinegar and seasoning.

It's pretty well kept in the dining area, and the staff has always been professional and quick.  I've never had a language barrier at this location, and I go in once a month or so.

Nothing earth shattering here folks, it's still a Subway, but it's a decent one.

I had a meeting in south philly today and lunch was catered by Subway. At first I felt let down that I'm in south philly with all these great sandwich places and I'm stuck eating subway. But boy was I wrong. The food was do good and I loved the lunch box they served it in. Also the cookie was so tasty. I have to admit that subway has upped their game and food was even better than panera and Corner bakery were we usually cater from in our blue bell office.
